⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Queen Eliza
node MSC · MSC · ⟦Queen Eliza:MSC:863997⟧

WHO   — Queen Eliza — the captive queen
WHAT  — The queen of Castle Garland — captured and held by the warlord Maharito, whose rescue is the whole goal of Milon's climb and whose freedom is the victory itself.
WHERE — MSC · Milon's Secret Castle  Framework inputs: Milon's Secret Castle (Hudson Soft, NES 1988)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because a kingdom needs its ruler restored; because the warlord who took the castle took its queen with it; because freeing her is the one thing the whole long climb is for.
HOW   — By being found and freed — held deep within the stolen castle until the boy with bubbles reaches her and breaks the warlord's hold.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  The castle is mine no longer; I wait within my own walls for the small one who will not stop climbing.

